result.execSummary:
The defendant Kimberly J. Stockwell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Cases called at 8:59 AM: 20CT326, 21CT1062, 21CF1218, 21CF1357, 21CM144, 22CF123, 22CF321, 22CM151.
Defendant Kimberly J. Stockwell in custody and in court with Attorney Robert Allen Thorson.   Attorney Matthew Kirkpatrick in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Agreement has been reached. Victim/Witness statute complied with. Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
20CF123: Defendant pleads No Contest to Count 1: Felony Bail Jumping.
22CF321: Defendant pleads No Contest to Count 1: Battery To Law Enforcement Officer; Attempt and Count 2: Possession of Methamphetamine.
Court accepts the pleas and finds the Defendant guilty. Counsel makes statements regarding the plea agreement.
Sentence is Withheld and the Defendant is placed on 3 Years of Probation with the following conditions:
60 Days of Jail (Huber eligibility to be determined at a later date) stayed pending further order of the Court (22CF123). 
No contact with Detective Ryan Lambeseder except in his official capacity as a law enforcement officer. 
Write a letter of apology to Detective Lambeseder within 30 days; letter is to be given to the agent who will provide a copy to the State.
No contact with K.H. or  M.L. No contact with any known drug dealers/users except in a therapeutic setting. Contact with her adult children only if approved in writing by the agent ahead of time.
AODA and follow through with recommendations. Maintain absolute sobriety. 
Defendant not to consume/possess any alcohol or go into any taverns, bars, liquor stores/place where alcohol is primarily served/sold. 
Defendant not to consume/use/possess any illegal drugs/non-prescribed medications/controlled substances or drug paraphernalia. 
Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. 
Defendant is granted 69 days of sentence credit in 22CF321 and 22CF123. Remaining charges are dismissed and read in.
Status conference on May 20, 2022 at 09:00 am.
